   <talk_paragraph index="n384_magician_sandus-accepting" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n384_magician_sandus-accepting-a" mid="6" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Huh? How do you know what I'm going to ask you?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="5"><![CDATA[<html>$Magician Sanders$<BR>The world is full of wondrous magic. What you're about to ask me right now is one of them.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n384_magician_sandus-accepting-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n384_magician_sandus-accepting-b" mid="8" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Well I'm not THAT curious...</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="7"><![CDATA[<html>$Magician Sanders$<BR>I know you're here to ask me about the Heroes Assemble system.<BR>Your inquisitive eyes are overflowing with curiosity, begging me to tell you everything. Please don’t lie to yourself.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n384_magician_sandus-accepting-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n384_magician_sandus-accepting-acceptted" mid="10" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html><FONT color=#086171>Accept Quest</FONT></html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="9"><![CDATA[<html>$Companions for Adventurers - Heroes Assemble!$</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n384_magician_sandus-1" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n384_magician_sandus-1-a" mid="12" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>What's that?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="11"><![CDATA[<html>$Magician Sanders$<BR>I'm sure you already know about the companions called Heroes. They are the ones who magically appear to help you in times of distress. </html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n384_magician_sandus-1-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n384_magician_sandus-1-b" mid="14" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="13"><![CDATA[<html>$Magician Sanders$<BR>Are you saying that you don't know the existence of <FONT color=#a82424>Heroes</FONT> yet?!<BR>Amazing. I never thought there would still be people like you around...</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n384_magician_sandus-1-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n384_magician_sandus-1-c" mid="16" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Well I have my companions.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="15"><![CDATA[<html>$Magician Sanders$<BR>With a few <FONT color=#086171>Wonderful Exchange Coupons</FONT> you've brought to me, I'm showing you magic that will blow your mind. If you <FONT color=#a82424>Buy a Hero</FONT>, you will get a companion who follows you to battles and helps you fight those monsters.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n384_magician_sandus-1-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n384_magician_sandus-1-d" mid="18" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Well… Okay. But I already have some helpers...</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="17"><![CDATA[<html>$Magician Sanders$<BR>Hey hey! Don't compare my Heroes with those animals who only know how to collect gold!<BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>(Sanders hisses)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n384_magician_sandus-1-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n384_magician_sandus-1-e" mid="20" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>A list? Wow. So I can summon many Heroes at once?!</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="19"><![CDATA[<html>$Magician Sanders$<BR>If you get yourself a Hero, you can <FONT color=#a82424>right click</FONT> to contract him or her. The Hero will never leave you once they sign the contract, unless there are very special reasons. You can check them at the <FONT color=#a82424>list in Hero tab</FONT> in your Character Info window.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n384_magician_sandus-1-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n384_magician_sandus-1-f" mid="22" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>How do I select a Hero?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="21"><![CDATA[<html>$Magician Sanders$<BR>Of course not! You may contract several Heroes, but you can only summon <FONT color=#a82424>one</FONT>.<BR>Even if you have hired many Heroes, only the selected one will hunt with you and level up. Actually... Heroes are jealous creatures... <FONT color=#7e12d2>(Magician Sanders speaks softly like he doesn't want anyone else to hear that)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n384_magician_sandus-1-f" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n384_magician_sandus-1-g" mid="24" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>I see.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="23"><![CDATA[<html>$Magician Sanders$<BR>Select the Hero you want to call upon and press the [<FONT color=#a82424>Summon/FONT>] button. It's that simple! You will get a companion with just one click! Magic!</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n384_magician_sandus-1-g" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n384_magician_sandus-1-h" mid="26" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Huh? Then when do they appear?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="25"><![CDATA[<html>$Magician Sanders$<BR>Not only that, the Heroes are shy creatures and they don't appear when there are too many people around. They don't appear in towns so don't be suprised even if they don't appear when you summon them in towns.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n384_magician_sandus-1-h" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n384_magician_sandus-1-i" mid="28" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Being too shy is a problem.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="27"><![CDATA[<html>$Magician Sanders$<BR>Heroes will appear when you quietly hunt in dungeons. They appear when you are alone, or when there are only <FONT color=#a94407>2 members in a party</FONT>. But they will never appear when your party has 3 or more players.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n384_magician_sandus-1-i" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n384_magician_sandus-1-j" mid="30" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>What? You synthesize humans? That is kinda unethical don't you think...</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="29"><![CDATA[<html>$Magician Sanders$<BR>If you keep participating in battles with your Hero, your Hero will level up quickly. Those that have reached maximum level can be <FONT color=#a82424>synthesized to a higher grade</FONT> by using the <FONT color=#086171>synthesis item</FONT>.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n384_magician_sandus-1-j" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n384_magician_sandus-1-k" mid="32" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>......</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="31"><![CDATA[<html>$Magician Sanders$<BR>Have you been listening? I told you this is pure magic!<BR>I wanted to skip all the complicated explanation but I guess you need one. The Hero that has absorbed the energy is made up of molecules that make up his physical body and special souls that are in the memories of the Goddess. They pass through this beam that gets reflected from each other for an interaction to take place and a new molecule of...<FONT color=#7e12d2>(Sanders blabbers what is neither magic nor science)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n384_magician_sandus-1-k" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n384_magician_sandus-1-l" mid="34" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>I see. I would love to try it!</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="33"><![CDATA[<html>$Magician Sanders$<BR>Ehem. I'm sorry I guess that was too much information. To summarize, you can enter a contract with Heroes of higher grade using synthesis. I believe you don't need more explanation about the <FONT color=#086171>Hero Synthesis Device</FONT>.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n384_magician_sandus-1-l" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n384_magician_sandus-1-m" mid="36" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html><FONT color=#086171>(Receive Reward)</FONT></html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="35"><![CDATA[<html>$Quest Reward$</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n384_magician_sandus-1-m" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_question mid="37"><![CDATA[<html>$Magician Sanders$<BR>I knew you'd say that. <BR>Well let's see… Take a look at what Heroes you can get. </html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
